    "recap_headline": "",
    "recap_text": "LYNCHBURG, VA. \u2013\nTrailing 11-8 in the top of the ninth inning, the Missouri State Bears plated four runs to top the Liberty Flames 12-11 Saturday afternoon at Worthington Field at Liberty Baseball Stadium.\nMissouri State catcher Carter Bergman led off the ninth with his eighth home run of the season and center fielder Caden Bogenpohl singled back through the middle of the diamond with one out to score two runs to take a 12-11 lead.\nFor the second straight day, Liberty moved the tying run into scoring position with two outs in the ninth. However, reliever Tyler Charlton was able to record the final out to seal the victory for the Bears.\nFlames designated hitter\nJordan Jaffe\nhad three hits, including a double, drove in a run and scored a run in the contest. In addition, right fielder\nRyan Drumm\nhad two hits, was hit by a pitch, knocked in two runs and scored four times for Liberty.\nFlames shortstop\nTanner Marsh\nhit his second home run of the season.\nLiberty drops to 12-5 overall and 0-2 in CUSA. Missouri State ups its record to 12-6 overall and 2-0 in conference play.\nBox Score Highlights\nRecords:\nMissouri State (12-6, 2-0 CUSA); Liberty (12-5, 0-2 CUSA)\nLocation:\nLynchburg, Va. (Worthington Field at Liberty Baseball Stadium)\nWP:\nLance Wade (1-1) |\nLP:\nAydan Decker-Perry (1-2) |\nSV:\nTyler Charlton (3)\nScoring Summary\n1\nst\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Sorenson grounds out,\nRyan Drumm\nscores, 1-0\n2\nnd\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Roessler singles, Atkinson scores, 1-1\n2\nnd\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Marsh homers, Campos scores, 3-1\n4\nth\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Roessler singles, Bergman scores, 3-2\n4\nth\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Beaman singles, Roessler and Fyffe scores, 4-3\n4\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Hvidsten singles, DeCandido scores, 4-4\n4\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Drumm reaches on a fielder's choice, Marsh, Campos and Hvidsten score on a throwing error, 7-4\n4\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Barone singles, Drumm scores, 8-4\n6\nth\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Gollert homers, Sutherland, Bogenpohl and Roessler score, 8-8\n6\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Jaffe doubles, Drumm scores, 10-8\n8\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Sorenson singles, Jaffe scores, 11-8\n9\nth\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Bergman homers, 11-9\n9\nth\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Kragel double, Cermenelli scores, 11-10\n9\nth\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Bogenpohl singles, Callahan scores, 12-11\nNotable Numbers\n- Missouri State outhit Liberty, 13-12, in the contest. The Bears committed three errors. The Flames made one.\n- Liberty left 11 men on base. Missouri State left nine men on base.\n- Flames reliever Aydan Decker-Perry, fourth of five Liberty pitchers in the contest, takes the loss. The right-hander allowed four runs on five hits over 1 1/3-plus innings. He struck out one and did not walk a batter.\n- The seventh of eight pitchers for Missouri State, reliever Lance Wade records the win. He struck out the only batter he faced in the game.\n- For the second day in a row, Tyler Charlton earns a save for the Bears. The right-hander pitched a scoreless ninth inning, yielding one hit. He struck out two and walked one.\n- Right fielder Taeg Gollert hit a grand slam for the Bears. It was his fourth home run of the season.\n- Missouri State left fielder Gabe Roessler went 3-for-3 with a walk, driving in two runs and scoring two runs.\nBeyond the Box Score\n- With their victory, Missouri State takes the first two games of the three-game series to capture the first CUSA series for both teams.\n- In both games of the series, the Bears have overcome deficits late. On Friday, Missouri State took the lead with two runs in the eighth. Today, the Bears took the lead with four runs in the ninth.\n- Jaffe records his second three-hit game and his third multi-hit game of the season.\n- Drumm also posted his third multi-hit game of the year.\n- With his home run in the second home run, Marsh extends his hitting streak to 14 games to tie his career-high of 14 games. He also has reached base in every game this season.\nUp Next\nLiberty and Missouri State wrap up their three-game CUSA series tomorrow. Game time is set for 11 a.m."
